reviews.review_text: Local, multigenerational family run business. Longliner Seafoods never disappoints. I ve been coming here for a few years now for my seafood, and could never go anywhere else - it is always super fresh, and super delicious. Their organic spring salmon is some of the best I ve ever had (highly recommend), and their smoked salmon selection is fantastic. I always go for the peppered nuggets (super moist and flavourful), the double smoked, and the cold smoked spring - they re the only people I ve seen who cold smoke spring salmon! The service is always wonderful and they often go above and beyond. It s a bit pricey, however it s expected for the quality and location. I have and will continue recommending this place!
Even if it looks busy, get in there and buy the Candied maple salmon. They do get to people pretty quickly. The salmon was still tender and the flavor was perfect with beer.
Super tasty smoked salmon. They are a bit pricy but it was worth it. We tried garlic and honey salmon. I prefer the honey salmon but others in my party are split 50 50.

Amazing salmon in all different tastes and flavors! Definitely one of the stand out stalls for me at the market. I only ordered a few pieces of smoked salmon since I didn t have anywhere to store the food, but I wish I did because this fish is super well done! The maple glazed salmon nuggets are the best. The staff here was also really helpful in providing us recommendations and answering questions so kudos to the team.

Bought wild King salmon and seafoods is very fresh. Caroline & Mangi provided great customer service. They are the best! The owner Dave is friendly and helpful too. I would highly recommend buying their seafoods.

They have a good selection of seafood and more reasonable prices compared to Longliner on the other side of Granville Public Market. Their products are all very similar in quality. They also sell foil packaged salmon that does not need to be refrigerated. Good idea for any gifts to bring back home.
The candied salmon from this counter service fish spot in the Granville Market is amazing. By amazing, think: Its like crack. Yeah. Its that good. Really, really good.
If I could add more stars, I  would. Amazing Pepper Salmon Nuggets..done the right way.  Moist and delicious. Best ever!
I got a little bit of all the smoked fish. The double smoked salmon sticks are some of the best smoked salmon Ive had. Service was also great.
Seafood was looking good small nice seafood place inside food market at Granville Island
The maple syrup candied salmon is worth the hype. Not overly sweet. It s yummy!
The smoked salmon is totally worth the drive and the parking hassle of Granville island. A must try!
Nice place. Great customer service. Salmon was super delicious and very fresh.

Im celiac and have not had crab cakes for over a decade. We went there on Sunday and found out their crab cakes were gluten free. Oh my goodness they were so tasty!!! We are going to be buying crab cakes from there for the rest of my life!!

Great candied salmon and amazing service! We were helped and when we told him we would buy 3 small pieces to try first, he gave us those pieces for free to try. We really appreciated that. After trying them, we bought a box of them!

In Granville Island market. Parking a real pain in butt sometimes. This is an excellent fishmonger, lots of specialty items like caviar and king crab. Lots of different smoked fish. Good prices. Fast attentive counter staff.
Best place in Vancouver to buy candied and smoked salmon! On top of that, the staff are absolutely lovely and I always leave with a smile. Highly recommend this gem on the island!
Bought the sealed smoked salmon to take back to Ontario. Ate it 3 weeks later and it was very good with capers, cream cheese, and red onion.

Longliner has some of the freshest fish in Vancouver and the guys Dave and Scott know it all. They can answer all your questions and have delicious smoked products to meet all of your seafood lovers demands!
Young Nick served my husband Vic yesterday with his Lox purchase, saying best service there ever, and that Nick should give the other Servers lessons on how to slice and psck.  GOOD JOB NICK!
Best seafood Ive ever had.  I cant go to Grandville Island wothout leaving with a absolutely stunning peice of organic spring fillers.  I swear to God it is like halibuit its so fresh!
Really friendly service, tasty smoked salmon bites (including maple syrup glazed) ready to eat
Double smoked salmon is gold!!! Also, buy a pound their salmon jerky for go-to protein amazing. I eat that all summer.
Super tasty and flavorful smoked salmon. Pretty expensive for the amount but 100% worth it to try!
The salmon is unbelievable. Never had anything so tasty.  Need to bring home lots cause I know I won t get this anywhere else!
Pepper smoked salmon is probably the best smoked salmon Ive ever tasted ... so tender!!! Yumm...
The smoked salmon they sell is to die for. They also have super fresh seafood. My favorite place in Vancouver.
Always impressed with the quality of fresh fish. Fishing family you can trust.
Always fresh and wonderful customer service
Nick was fantastic, very helpful and knowledgeable. Great experience!
Go directly to their backdoor when lineups to get into Granville Island Market are prohibitive.
Great customer service, very knowledgeable about their product and sanitary.
Fresh & high quality seafood with a focus on sustainability!
Best fresh salmon ever
Yummy
Smoked salmon was good
Best place in town
Its actually more delicious than I thought and goes well with beer I think Ill buy it again and eat it because its so special.
Their salmon is very delicious and has a domestic flavor. I forgot to take a photo because it was so delicious. It is the red color of the sauce.

Stopped by to pick up a small bowl of maple syrup glazed candy salmon and smoked peppered salmon. You can do a half and half 100g bowl so you can try a little bit of both. The smoked peppered salmon was a bit dry and the maple syrup salmon wasnt as sweet as I was expecting. Overall it made for a small, tasty treat. The staff were very nice and quick with service.

Definitely one of the busier joints in the Granville Market and had a big line on Saturday at lunch time. Came back later and no wait. Lots of smoked fish selections and of course a ton of salmon varieties. Solid flavors.

Going for a healthier snack option, got my ready-to-eat seafood fix from Longliner Seafoods.  Smoked Mackerel for savoury and Maple Syrup Glazed Salmon Nuggets for sweet craving.  Both fish are of good quality, texture and flavour are on point, one can tell great care has been poured over these creations by tasting them.  The seafood selection is vast, the fish is stacked neatly, the display looks clean and pleasant.  This shop is a great stop for quality seafoods at Granville Market.
Poki! $9 for small cup to satisfy craving.
A little hesitant to try the candy salmon but it was delicious
Good smoked salmon!
4.5 stars! Always a go to place for fresh seafood when in Vancouver!!Some may say they are costly, however I think their prices are very reasonable!
This is the most beautiful fresh fish stall I ever seen in Vancouver for now!
new moss
It was alright. It wasn t bad at all. Although for $35 I was expecting the crab to be fresher and juicier.
Wasn t the biggest fan of the poke and salmon. It was expensive for such small portions and for the taste

Hi.........normally I would rate you *5* without a second thought but today I have to drop that to a 3 because yesterday my husband picked up some Dungeness Crab for $34.19  0.222kg and it left an awful lot to be desired.  We have had your crab so very many times previous to yesterday and it has been marvellous!! but yesterdays was not good.  It was mushy and had a fishy smell that we have never detected before.  I ate it but I have to say, I kind of buried it in cocktail sauce so I might not notice the mushy texture;  my husband didnt eat all of his portion which is a complete rarity for him - hes like Mikie - he eat anything.  I just wanted to let you know we are disappointed but want to continue buying from you but we may just think twice first.   I am sorry to be negative because weve never been disappointed before.  thanks for reading..... Rose Jorgenson-Mills
Their customer service needs improvement. I tried a variety of their ready-to-eat salmon treats. They were just alright.

Charge premium prices for fish but quality is questionable. I have on more than one occasion seen worms crawling on the fish in the case (flicked off by the staff and served anyway). Today I bought a piece of cod ($25/lb) with a sign that said fresh and local only to get it home and find a big parasitic worm next to it. From what I can tell online, this only happens when the fresh fish is not filleted right away but is kept whole, giving the worm a chance to borrow through from the fishs intestine out of the fish. Sure, its probably fine when cooked thoroughly. I did cook it but could not enjoy it and threw half of it away. Found another cooked worm on my dinner plate and just couldnt finish it.
Fish out front looked great, but bought a pack to take home and was nowhere near as nice.

I bought a red spring salmon fillet on Saturday. Had it for dinner the same day. I was given ice to pack with it. I brought it home immediately to the refrigerator. The fish had a very fishy smell to it. That indicates to me its not too fresh. Ive had salmon from other grocers to compare & no other places had fishy smell to my salmon. Very fresh & high quality fish is supposed to be scent less & not fishy. I wonder if its because not too many people were buying the spring salmon fillets & they were there for a while. Im kind of disappointed in this place seeing it is supposedly a high end seafood store in a high end location. I doubt Ill be back to do business again.
I paid for two packages of smoked salmon and the cashier only wrapped up 1 not happy with this place make sure you check your packages after you buy them

Pretty disappointed with my experience. I bought the candied salmon and paid with my credit card, they called me back to say their internet was down so they would have to use the old school method of swiping my card with the imprinter - they broke the chip on my credit card with the imprinter so now Im in Vancouver for 2 days with no way of paying for items on my card. When I called to tell them what happened they offered nothing in compensation (not that I expect much) and basically said sorry, thats too bad. I wont be back. The candied salmon wasnt worth the experience in terms of quality or customer service.
Terribly ran, thought I d give them a shot and I will not be returning. Wasted a large sum of money here and all the fish were filled with worm like parasites. The staff were also extremely rude.

Im tired of vendors who think their personal mission to enforce mandates are more important than relating graciously with their customers. Longliner is one of those. Im unimpressed, get your priorities straight.

Rude customer service  .I have a mask exemption and the employees laughed at me and said that doesn t exist!!!! Discrimination at its finest! Will never shop here again! I will let everyone know how rude your staff is!
Any person who descriminate against their fellow man does not deserve Business,not impressed.
